 to add a summary that notes, \\\"API-only artifact; it has a transitive dependency on jakarta.annotation-api; no provider or database is required for API-level compile or native reachability; there is an existing failure from interface changes.\\\" I should also mention that there are no environment or system properties needed. The deterministic setup is empty.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"jakarta.persistence-api is an API/specification artifact with only jakarta.annotation-api as a compile dependency; meaningful coverage is reachable with annotations, interfaces, exceptions, and test-local SPI fakes without adding a provider, database, Docker image, or environment/system property. The reported failure is caused by API interface additions in 4.0.0-M5, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. If covering Persistence bootstrap behavior, use a test-local PersistenceProviderResolver via PersistenceProviderResolverHolder and restore it after the test; do not add a real JPA provider just to exercise the API artifact.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests that attempt real EntityManagerFactory/database operations would require an external JPA provider and likely a JDBC/database setup, but that would primarily test the provider rather than jakarta.persistence-api.\",\n    \"Existing hand-written stubs implementing Query or TypedQuery must be updated for new 4.0.0-M5 abstract methods such as setParameters(Object...).\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c9afc75fff99cce016a3ec31a77e48190bc5f3294090475dd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1510, "output": 756, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26842, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp"